Business Brief -- Borden Inc.:
   Firm Posts 4th-Period Net
   Fell 58%, Including Charge
Sales for the quarter slipped 3% to $1.85 billion from
$1.90 billion a year ago. Borden cited lower cheese prices,
increased raw milk costs, and intense competition in the
snack business, among other factors.
   Net income for the full year fell 19% to $294.9 million,
or $2 a share, from $363.6 million, or $2.46 a share, in
1990. Without the charge, net income would have fallen 7% to
$338.9 million or $2.30 a share. Sales fell 5% to $7.24
billion from $7.63 billion.